<h2>Solar Incentives in Fort Worth</h2>

<p>Fort Worth residents have access to several valuable solar incentives that significantly reduce the cost of installation. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost through 2032, before stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. This credit applies to all components of the solar installation, including panels, inverters, mounting equipment, and labor costs. Additionally, Texas offers property tax exemptions for solar installations, meaning the added home value from solar panels won't increase your property taxes. While Texas doesn't currently offer statewide solar rebates, Oncor provides interconnection services and net metering opportunities that allow customers to receive retail rate credits for excess solar energy fed back into the grid. Some Fort Worth residents may also qualify for local utility programs or financing options that further reduce upfront costs, making solar installation more accessible across different income levels.</p>

